text: Anne of York (10 August, 1439 - 1476) was a member of the House of York in England, a branch of the English Royal Family. She was the second and eldest surviving daughter of Richard Plantagenet, 3rd Duke of York and Cecily Neville, Duchess of York. == References == Category:1439 births Category:1476 deaths Category:House of York Category:English nobility Category:Deaths in childbirth
